# Add the bluetooth signals to this file.
# Lines starting with "#" will be ignored
#
# Format of file:
#
# For running one IR Signal
# bluetoothSignal:sig:deviceName:signalName
#
# The first argument is the bluetooth signal, f.eks: 1000 (Or any string)
# The second argument indicates if it is a signal or sequence sig/seq
# The two last arguments indicate device name and signal name
#
# For running a sequence of IR Signals
# bluetoothSignal:seq:sequenceName
#
# The first argument is the bluetooth signal, for example: 1000 (Or any string)
# The second argument indicates if it is a signal or sequence sig/seq
# The last argument is the sequence name
#
# The next lines are a suggestion for a bluetooth protocol and can be altered
#
# TVSignals: 1000-1999
# RecieverSignals: 2000-2999
2100:sig:Reciever:On
2101:sig:Reciever:Off
2201:sig:Reciever:Up
2202:sig:Reciever:Down
2203:sig:Reciever:Left
2204:sig:Reciever:Right
2205:sig:Reciever:VolUp
2206:sig:Reciever:VolDown
2209:sig:Reciever:Enter
2210:sig:Reciever:Menu
#
# TVDekoderSignals: 3000-3999
# AppleTVSignals: 4000-4999
4100:sig:AppleTV:Home
4201:sig:AppleTV:Up
4202:sig:AppleTV:Down
4203:sig:AppleTV:Left
4204:sig:AppleTV:Right
4209:sig:AppleTV:Enter
4210:sig:AppleTV:Menu
#
# ProjectorSignals: 5000-5999
5100:sig:Projector:On
5101:sig:Projector:Off
5201:sig:Projector:Up
5202:sig:Projector:Down
5203:sig:Projector:Left
5204:sig:Projector:Right
5210:sig:Projector:Menu
#
# X-BoxSignals: 6000-6999
# Canvas:7000-7999
7000:sig:Canvas:Down
7001:sig:Canvas:Up
#
# SequenceSignals: 9000-9999